  "texts": [
    "Essentially, the conduction electron's polarization is transferred in a single spin-flip process by creating an excitation in the spin bath, thus preventing the electronic kinetic energy from further relaxation.After a short coherent dynamics, there is a Markovian regime with an exponential decay with a time scale J 2 /t 0.",
    "For J/t 0 < ∼ 1.5, we find an excellent agreement between numerical data and these approximate analytical results.For J/t 0 > ∼ 2, eventually, on average, no net energy transfer occurs and the dynamics are mostly dominated by oscillations.",
    "The steady-state values of expectation values can be understood from considering the decomposition of the initial state into eigenstates in small systems, due to the local nature of the physics in the large J/t 0 > 2 limit.",
    "Numerical illustration of relaxation dynamicsThe initial state with a complete parallel alignment of all localized spins and antiparallel spin orientation of the conduction electron belongs to the subspace S z total = 1 2 (L -1).",
    "In principle, this coincides with the total spin quantum number of the ground state of the Kondolattice model with one itinerant electron."
  ],
